WEBVTT

00:06.639 --> 00:10.640
♪

00:10.679 --> 00:12.759
In a Kentucky mall,
you can meet

00:12.800 --> 00:15.359
a very famous taxidermy bear.

00:15.400 --> 00:18.280
This is my first time
seeing the cocaine bear.

00:18.320 --> 00:19.800
The what bear?

00:19.839 --> 00:22.559
Yes, the cocaine bear.

00:22.600 --> 00:25.399
There's a reason why
he's called the cocaine bear.

00:25.440 --> 00:28.640
This story is amazing.

00:28.679 --> 00:30.920
♪

00:30.960 --> 00:35.880
One day in the woods, a bear
finds a huge bag of drugs.

00:35.920 --> 00:38.719
And the bear got high.

00:38.759 --> 00:39.960
[ Bear growling ]

00:40.000 --> 00:43.039
The cocaine was 95% pure.

00:43.079 --> 00:45.200
No, really, they found him
laying there

00:45.240 --> 00:47.600
with the cocaine around him.

00:47.640 --> 00:48.679
[ Chuckles ]

00:48.719 --> 00:52.000
That's a very interesting
story in itself.

00:52.039 --> 00:56.320
But this is the origin
story of the cocaine bear,

00:56.359 --> 01:00.359
featuring the larger-than-life
man who started it all.

01:00.399 --> 01:02.200
He was mercurial
and mysterious.

01:02.240 --> 01:03.719
He lived on the edge.

01:03.759 --> 01:08.519
He had a James Bond wristwatch
that shot tear gas.

01:08.560 --> 01:10.239
These are Kentucky Blue Bloods

01:10.280 --> 01:12.920
that got together to go
into full-time smuggling.

01:12.959 --> 01:15.000
He was a bad dude!

01:15.040 --> 01:17.040
This is such a powerful story.

01:17.079 --> 01:20.879
It has corruption,
it has murder.

01:20.920 --> 01:24.439
Judge John Wood was fatally
wounded by a single gunshot.

01:24.480 --> 01:27.640
Drugs, murders, gun running,
you name it.

01:27.680 --> 01:30.079
Holy crap, you would
never believe it,

01:30.120 --> 01:31.560
but it did actually happen.

01:31.599 --> 01:35.040
Believe it or not,
this story even has cows...

01:35.079 --> 01:36.200
on drugs.

01:36.239 --> 01:38.439
Oh, come on!
[ Laughs ]

01:38.480 --> 01:42.280
This is the true story
of the cocaine bear.

01:42.319 --> 01:44.599
You wouldn't forget it.
Let's put it that way.

01:51.120 --> 02:00.879
♪

02:00.920 --> 02:03.319
The backwoods of the
Chattahoochee National Forest

02:03.359 --> 02:07.799
in North Georgia
are stark and remote.

02:07.840 --> 02:11.360
In December 1985, a hunter
finds something here

02:11.400 --> 02:13.599
that sparks a legend.

02:13.639 --> 02:15.400
♪

02:15.439 --> 02:20.800
This legend has grown
to be quite a story.

02:20.840 --> 02:22.599
And in 2023, that legend

02:22.639 --> 02:26.280
is brought to life
by an incredible movie.

02:26.319 --> 02:28.199
[ Bear roars ]

02:28.240 --> 02:31.400
And soon the whole world
is talking about it.

02:31.439 --> 02:34.080
Number one trend on Twitter.
Everyone's talking about this.

02:34.120 --> 02:35.199
[ Bear roaring ]

02:35.240 --> 02:37.599
A bear did cocaine!

02:37.639 --> 02:41.280
This will be the winner
of the decade probably.

02:41.319 --> 02:43.599
Cocaine Bear, Fran.

02:43.639 --> 02:45.400
Take One. Mark.

02:45.439 --> 02:49.240
♪

02:49.280 --> 02:52.360
Well, my name
is Francis Bishop Wiley.

02:52.400 --> 02:55.199
And in December of 1985,

02:55.240 --> 02:58.639
I was Assistant
Special Agent in Charge

02:58.680 --> 03:01.080
of the Georgia Bureau
of Investigation,

03:01.120 --> 03:02.280
in Gainseville, Georgia,

03:02.319 --> 03:05.879
and right now I'm retired.

03:05.919 --> 03:07.400
I received a call at the office

03:07.439 --> 03:11.840
from a game warden
in Fanon County, Georgia.

03:11.879 --> 03:15.000
And he advised that a hunter
had found a bear

03:15.039 --> 03:18.120
in the woods on a mountain

03:18.159 --> 03:22.199
and that there was a parachute
and a duffel bag close by.

03:22.240 --> 03:25.199
I dispatched two of my agents
to the scene.

03:25.240 --> 03:27.400
They radioed back and advised me

03:27.439 --> 03:31.680
that there indeed was a bear,
parachute, and duffel bag.

03:31.719 --> 03:33.479
So I said,
well, this is very strange.

03:33.520 --> 03:36.840
I mean, very odd that we would
even find something like this.

03:36.879 --> 03:39.199
I told them to take it
to the Georgia crime lab

03:39.240 --> 03:42.879
in Atlanta,
and they did take the duffel bag

03:42.919 --> 03:46.159
and found residue
of cocaine on it.

03:46.199 --> 03:48.240
There was no cocaine
in the duffel bag,

03:48.280 --> 03:49.960
so where did the cocaine go?

03:50.000 --> 03:51.719
Well, the bear ate it.

03:51.759 --> 03:57.120
♪

03:57.159 --> 04:02.520
♪

04:02.560 --> 04:05.400
The bizarre story of this bear
and what happened

04:05.439 --> 04:09.960
actually begins
three months before.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.400
[ Thud ]

04:12.439 --> 04:15.080
In the middle of the night,
a Knoxville resident

04:15.120 --> 04:18.959
is awakened by a sound
from his backyard.

04:19.000 --> 04:20.319
It wasn't until
the next morning

04:20.360 --> 04:23.720
that he looked in his driveway

04:23.759 --> 04:26.439
and immediately
called the police.

04:26.480 --> 04:30.000
♪

04:30.040 --> 04:31.199
My name is Jimmy Jones.

04:31.240 --> 04:33.360
I'm a retired
Knox County sheriff.

04:33.399 --> 04:34.759
From the time
I was 16 years old,

04:34.800 --> 04:37.639
I knew I wanted to be
in law enforcement.

04:37.680 --> 04:39.120
We were just
in the office that day.

04:39.160 --> 04:42.079
It was a normal day,
just like any other day.

04:42.120 --> 04:45.560
The call came in from dispatch.
It was an elderly gentleman,

04:45.600 --> 04:48.759
and he said that there was
a gentleman out in his driveway

04:48.800 --> 04:50.360
who was trespassing,

04:50.399 --> 04:53.680
and if the police didn't come he
would take care of it himself.

04:53.720 --> 04:57.879
♪

04:57.920 --> 05:01.600
The "trespasser" is the dead
body of a skydiver,

05:01.639 --> 05:04.839
and JJ is called
to the crime scene.

05:04.879 --> 05:14.639
♪

05:14.680 --> 05:16.839
This is a very quiet
community, usually.

05:16.879 --> 05:19.800
There's very little crime,
very little happens.

05:19.839 --> 05:22.600
When we arrived on the scene,
the individual was found

05:22.639 --> 05:26.079
in the gravel driveway area
between the houses.

05:26.120 --> 05:28.600
♪

05:28.639 --> 05:31.120
We were surprised to see
this individual here.

05:31.160 --> 05:33.959
His parachute was kind of
wadded up beside him,

05:34.000 --> 05:37.279
like it hadn't fully opened.

05:37.319 --> 05:39.600
The gentleman was deceased.

05:39.639 --> 05:44.120
There was a duffel bag that
was hooked to the individual.

05:44.160 --> 05:46.000
The duffel bag
contained somewhere

05:46.040 --> 05:50.079
between 30 and 40 packages
marked USA.

05:50.120 --> 05:52.240
All of them were labelled
the same way.

05:52.279 --> 05:54.439
We knew when we cut into it,
it was still moist,

05:54.480 --> 05:57.800
and the smell would just
hit you in the face.

05:57.839 --> 06:00.800
It was a very high quality
of cocaine.

06:00.839 --> 06:03.759
♪

06:03.800 --> 06:07.879
Somewhere between 30
and 40 kilos of cocaine.

06:07.920 --> 06:10.759
It was probably worth
hundreds of millions.

06:10.800 --> 06:12.399
I was amazed.

06:12.439 --> 06:16.120
And I was just a kid. I mean,
I wasn't but 24, 25 years old.

06:16.160 --> 06:18.000
I had never seen
anything like that.

06:18.040 --> 06:20.160
It was like holy crap, you know?

06:20.199 --> 06:22.360
This-- You would never
believe this happened

06:22.399 --> 06:24.879
in sleepy, little, old
Knoxville, Tennessee.

06:24.920 --> 06:27.959
[ Laughs ]

06:28.000 --> 06:31.839
We continued to look
at the body to evaluate it.

06:31.879 --> 06:35.680
There was at least one attack
knife along with some daggers

06:35.720 --> 06:40.120
or spears that were actually
in a sheath on his arm,

06:40.160 --> 06:41.519
night vision goggles.

06:41.560 --> 06:45.519
There was about $5,000
in US currency.

06:45.560 --> 06:48.000
There were precious
and semi-precious stones

06:48.040 --> 06:50.240
in a money belt.

06:50.279 --> 06:53.519
He had some gold Krugerrands.

06:53.560 --> 06:55.399
Nobody knew what
a Krugerrand was.

06:55.439 --> 06:56.800
We heard of 'em,
but nobody actually--

06:56.839 --> 06:59.319
I don't think anybody
had ever seen 'em.

06:59.360 --> 07:02.040
They were gold, and they have
like a little kangaroo

07:02.079 --> 07:04.519
or an animal on the front.

07:04.560 --> 07:09.399
♪

07:09.439 --> 07:13.839
Initially we had no clue
what had happened.

07:13.879 --> 07:17.079
None of this is making sense
for JJ and his team.

07:17.120 --> 07:19.759
Who is this guy in the driveway?

07:19.800 --> 07:23.000
There's some questions that
really haven't been answered.

07:23.040 --> 07:24.360
He was mysterious.

07:24.399 --> 07:28.360
He looked a lot
like a soldier of fortune.

07:28.399 --> 07:30.879
He had a 9mm Browning
high powered pistol

07:30.920 --> 07:34.199
that was loaded
with Teflon-coated 9mm bullets.

07:34.240 --> 07:37.800
Those are the bullets that will
penetrate a bulletproof vest.

07:37.839 --> 07:40.040
He also had a wristwatch

07:40.079 --> 07:43.519
that was like
a James Bond wristwatch,

07:43.560 --> 07:46.800
but it wasn't one that you would
get out of a cereal box.

07:46.839 --> 07:52.759
It was actually a high-quality
watch that shot tear gas.

07:52.800 --> 07:57.120
I was amazed every time
something came off his body,

07:57.160 --> 08:00.199
a piece of equipment
or whatever it was.

08:00.240 --> 08:03.399
I mean, it was just more
and more and more.

08:03.439 --> 08:07.920
He also had some
very expensive shoes.

08:07.959 --> 08:11.000
In an odd fact that a lot
of people noted at the time,

08:11.040 --> 08:13.680
he was wearing Gucci loafers.

08:13.720 --> 08:15.120
[ Ding! ]

08:15.160 --> 08:17.800
♪

08:17.839 --> 08:20.160
I mean, we were still trying
to put pieces together.

08:20.199 --> 08:22.160
We really didn't have anything.

08:22.199 --> 08:26.759
Then as more agencies
became involved,

08:26.800 --> 08:28.319
we ultimately found out

08:28.360 --> 08:30.879
that the plane had crashed
in North Carolina.

08:30.920 --> 08:35.639
♪

08:35.679 --> 08:38.639
The wreckage of the Cessna 404
is still scattered

08:38.679 --> 08:41.600
across this ridge
of the Nantahala Mountains.

08:41.639 --> 08:44.759
We did hear that a body
had been found in Knoxville

08:44.799 --> 08:46.679
of someone who parachuted
out of a plane,

08:46.720 --> 08:49.159
and evidently,
the parachute didn't open.

08:49.200 --> 08:51.399
At this time, it kind of appears

08:51.440 --> 08:53.840
that that may be involved
with this.

08:53.879 --> 08:56.080
♪

08:56.120 --> 08:58.360
The location of the plane
in North Carolina

08:58.399 --> 08:59.799
is more than 100 miles

08:59.840 --> 09:03.679
from the body
of the mysterious parachutist.

09:03.720 --> 09:06.279
The aircraft provides
a vital clue--

09:06.320 --> 09:09.639
It's registered to a man
from Lexington, Kentucky.

09:14.159 --> 09:16.399
In Lexington,
the information filters down

09:16.440 --> 09:18.600
to the local papers.

09:18.639 --> 09:23.200
♪

09:23.240 --> 09:27.519
I was a investigative reporter
at the Lexington Herald Leader

09:27.559 --> 09:28.799
in Kentucky

09:28.840 --> 09:32.159
from about 1979 to 1987.

09:32.200 --> 09:34.320
♪

09:34.360 --> 09:37.480
The body was identified
as Andrew Thornton.

09:37.519 --> 09:40.919
And that erupted the newsroom
at the time.

09:40.960 --> 09:43.679
♪

09:43.720 --> 09:44.799
Drew Thornton was someone

09:44.840 --> 09:46.320
who had been
in a position of authority,

09:46.360 --> 09:48.960
a police officer
who came from privilege.

09:49.000 --> 09:52.159
He was a soldier, had, you know,
been wounded in combat.

09:52.200 --> 09:54.480
Personally, I wasn't
all that surprised

09:54.519 --> 09:58.000
when I heard that he was dead
in Knoxville in a driveway,

09:58.039 --> 09:59.600
having fallen out of a plane.

09:59.639 --> 10:03.000
He had lived on the edge
and was--

10:03.039 --> 10:05.039
His luck had run out.

10:08.039 --> 10:13.159
♪

10:13.200 --> 10:18.240
♪

10:18.279 --> 10:20.799
With the body identified,
police trace Thornton's

10:20.840 --> 10:24.639
flight path all the way back
to North Georgia.

10:24.679 --> 10:26.840
We started receiving
more information

10:26.879 --> 10:28.960
that there was more cocaine
that had been dumped

10:29.000 --> 10:31.200
along the way of his journey.

10:31.240 --> 10:34.799
♪

10:34.840 --> 10:37.679
The duffel bag Drew Thornton
had strapped to his body

10:37.720 --> 10:39.000
when he died

10:39.039 --> 10:41.639
was of the same make,
color, and type

10:41.679 --> 10:45.639
that they found close
to the bear in Georgia.

10:45.679 --> 10:49.879
The incredible story is quickly
picked up by the TV networks.

10:49.919 --> 10:52.320
The medical examiner says
the bear had been dead

10:52.360 --> 10:54.200
for at least six weeks.

10:54.240 --> 10:57.320
GBI agents recovered
none of the cocaine.

10:57.360 --> 10:59.759
They said it could have been
blown away by the wind

10:59.799 --> 11:01.320
or simply dissolved.

11:01.360 --> 11:02.799
One thing's for sure--

11:02.840 --> 11:07.720
The bear did not eat
75 pounds of the stuff.

11:07.759 --> 11:11.240
We believe that the duffel bag
that was found in Fanon County

11:11.279 --> 11:12.840
next to the bear

11:12.879 --> 11:17.320
also had 75 pounds of cocaine.

11:17.360 --> 11:21.159
When we found it,
there was no cocaine.

11:21.200 --> 11:24.399
There was 75 pounds
found with Andrew Thornton

11:24.440 --> 11:28.039
in a similar duffel bag
when he jumped to his death.

11:28.080 --> 11:30.120
♪

11:30.159 --> 11:32.440
So who really is
Andrew Thornton?

11:32.480 --> 11:35.600
And how is he
connected to the cocaine bear?

11:35.639 --> 11:37.799
To find answers, we need
to go back decades

11:37.840 --> 11:41.120
to the heartland of Kentucky's
blue-blood society.

11:41.159 --> 11:48.480
♪

11:48.519 --> 11:55.679
♪

11:55.720 --> 11:57.200
My name is Ron Bryant.

11:57.240 --> 12:00.399
I was historian for
the Kentucky State Park System

12:00.440 --> 12:04.519
and director of Waveland State
historic site.

12:04.559 --> 12:09.399
My family has been in Kentucky
for over 200 years.

12:09.440 --> 12:11.159
Kentucky historian Ron Bryant

12:11.200 --> 12:14.080
is a distant relative
of Daniel Boone.

12:14.120 --> 12:17.320
He knows Kentucky.

12:17.360 --> 12:18.879
There was always old jokes
in Kentucky

12:18.919 --> 12:21.200
about everyone being related
to each other.

12:21.240 --> 12:24.320
Well, in some cases, the gene
pool was rather shallow,

12:24.360 --> 12:25.879
I've got to admit.

12:25.919 --> 12:28.279
♪

12:28.320 --> 12:31.000
But not with Andrew Thornton.

12:31.039 --> 12:33.600
Andrew was a child of privilege.

12:33.639 --> 12:35.000
None of this should have
ever happened

12:35.039 --> 12:37.480
according to the way
he was raised.

12:37.519 --> 12:42.000
When the news came
that Andrew Thornton had died

12:42.039 --> 12:44.519
and how he died,

12:44.559 --> 12:48.000
society was not only
in a state of shock.

12:48.039 --> 12:51.120
It was in a state
of absolute shock.

12:51.159 --> 12:53.879
♪

12:53.919 --> 12:57.519
Andrew Thornton II was the son

12:57.559 --> 13:01.240
of, uh, Andrew Carter Thornton.

13:01.279 --> 13:04.000
The Thorntons had
established themselves

13:04.039 --> 13:05.759
in the horse industry.

13:05.799 --> 13:07.960
And they knew their horses.

13:08.000 --> 13:11.000
And they, in fact,
had at least two derby winners.

13:11.039 --> 13:14.480
That's quite a feather
in anybody's cap right there.

13:14.519 --> 13:16.519
♪

13:20.320 --> 13:22.399
Andrew Thornton certainly
had the breeding--

13:22.440 --> 13:24.440
[ Chuckles ] It's funny
to use the word breeding

13:24.480 --> 13:26.080
for someone
from Lexington, Kentucky,

13:26.120 --> 13:28.360
because that never hardly
ever talks about people.

13:28.399 --> 13:29.559
It's only about horses.

13:29.600 --> 13:32.639
But he really did
have the breeding.

13:32.679 --> 13:34.960
Andrew Thornton entered
the University of Kentucky,

13:35.000 --> 13:36.480
but his heart wasn't in it.

13:36.519 --> 13:38.039
So he left the University
of Kentucky

13:38.080 --> 13:42.960
after a short period of time
and volunteered for combat.

13:43.000 --> 13:47.399
♪

13:47.440 --> 13:50.720
He went into the Army,
actually won a purple heart.

13:50.759 --> 13:55.960
And he particularly liked flying
and parachuting.

13:56.000 --> 14:04.639
♪

14:04.679 --> 14:09.399
In 1968, Thornton returns home
a hero and gets married.

14:09.440 --> 14:10.840
But it doesn't last.

14:10.879 --> 14:14.639
This man of action is looking
for his next thrill.

14:14.679 --> 14:18.799
He wanted something
that was not staid and safe.

14:18.840 --> 14:24.480
He wanted something that was,
shall we say, nearly dangerous.

14:24.519 --> 14:26.399
♪

14:26.440 --> 14:29.200
After having a very
distinguished military career,

14:29.240 --> 14:34.159
he came back, and he joined
the police department.

14:34.200 --> 14:39.279
Thornton liked the idea
of being a police officer

14:39.320 --> 14:42.440
because that was
an adventuresome life.

14:42.480 --> 14:44.720
♪

14:44.759 --> 14:46.000
My name is Jim Huggins.

14:46.039 --> 14:47.720
I was a supervisory
special agent

14:47.759 --> 14:50.200
for the FBI
in Lexington, Kentucky.

14:50.240 --> 14:54.399
from 1986
to 1995 when I retired.

14:54.440 --> 14:55.840
I worked very closely

14:55.879 --> 14:59.000
with the Kentucky State Police
Intelligence Bureau.

14:59.039 --> 15:04.320
♪

15:04.360 --> 15:06.799
In the '70s at that time,
there was a lot of

15:06.840 --> 15:08.600
drug activities
starting to show up,

15:08.639 --> 15:11.440
particularly around
the college campus area.

15:11.480 --> 15:13.679
It was becoming
a major crime problem

15:13.720 --> 15:17.799
for the local law enforcement
agencies at that time.

15:17.840 --> 15:19.399
The Lexington Police Department

15:19.440 --> 15:23.159
creates its first
narcotics squad.

15:23.200 --> 15:25.799
And the promise of action
is a huge draw

15:25.840 --> 15:29.159
for the young Andrew Thornton.

15:29.200 --> 15:31.519
He volunteered
for the Narcotics unit.

15:31.559 --> 15:34.559
His best friend, Bill Canan,
was already working there.

15:34.600 --> 15:37.080
Bill Canan came from
a much different background

15:37.120 --> 15:38.879
than Drew Thornton.

15:38.919 --> 15:41.200
His family was working class.

15:41.240 --> 15:45.200
Drew Thornton likes the fact
that Bill Canan is a tough guy.

15:45.240 --> 15:48.039
As a pair,
they're made for trouble.

15:48.080 --> 15:54.159
♪

15:54.200 --> 15:57.080
They were trying to infiltrate
student groups

15:57.120 --> 15:58.519
out at the University
of Kentucky,

15:58.559 --> 16:00.480
and they would hang out in bars

16:00.519 --> 16:04.519
and dress like
a regular student.

16:04.559 --> 16:09.600
There also were accusations that
they would arrest a drug dealer,

16:09.639 --> 16:11.440
confiscate his drugs,

16:11.480 --> 16:14.639
and then instead of turning them
into the evidence locker

16:14.679 --> 16:19.440
like they should have,
they'd keep them for themselves.

16:19.480 --> 16:20.799
There were allegations that

16:20.840 --> 16:24.879
they did in fact resell
some of the drugs.

16:24.919 --> 16:28.559
It wasn't too big a leap for
someone in a new narcotics squad

16:28.600 --> 16:31.000
to think that maybe if they just
held back a little bit

16:31.039 --> 16:33.320
of what, uh,
they had confiscated

16:33.360 --> 16:34.679
and then turned it back out
on the streets,

16:34.720 --> 16:36.639
that they could
increase their income.

16:36.679 --> 16:39.840
But why would a wealthy member
of the Lexington elite

16:39.879 --> 16:43.440
stoop to stealing drugs?

16:43.480 --> 16:45.960
Nobody really,
really, really knew

16:46.000 --> 16:47.600
what Andrew Thornton was doing.

16:47.639 --> 16:51.240
There had been rumors
that were going around

16:51.279 --> 16:54.679
that something was bad wrong
with Andrew.

16:54.720 --> 16:57.000
For Thornton, it may not
have been simply

16:57.039 --> 16:59.200
just to get some extra money.

16:59.240 --> 17:02.200
It may have been to do something

17:02.240 --> 17:04.799
that other people
couldn't do or wouldn't do.

17:04.839 --> 17:08.799
It would go along with his whole
soldier of fortune lifestyle

17:08.839 --> 17:11.160
that he cultivated.

17:11.200 --> 17:13.400
That would be his downfall,

17:13.440 --> 17:16.240
changing him from
a pillar of society

17:16.279 --> 17:19.640
into a pariah in society.

17:19.680 --> 17:23.400
The charmed life of Drew
Thornton is about to get darker

17:23.440 --> 17:27.440
on the way to a rendezvous...
with the cocaine bear.

17:38.720 --> 17:42.319
In 1975, the cocaine bear
was just a cub

17:42.359 --> 17:45.519
learning the bear way of life
in the woods of Georgia.

17:45.559 --> 17:48.880
♪

17:52.079 --> 17:56.400
Meanwhile more than 300 miles
away in Lexington, Kentucky,

17:56.440 --> 17:59.599
Drew Thornton is relishing
his role as a dirty cop

17:59.640 --> 18:02.319
with his tough guy partner
Bill Canan...

18:02.359 --> 18:04.680
a world away from his
respectable upbringing

18:04.720 --> 18:07.839
in Kentucky horse
breeding society.

18:07.880 --> 18:11.279
I think Andrew Thornton was one
of these types of individuals

18:11.319 --> 18:13.480
that's grown up
with a silver spoon,

18:13.519 --> 18:16.559
and they've gotten just about
anything they wanted.

18:16.599 --> 18:20.039
So to have this kind of thrill

18:20.079 --> 18:22.000
is something that excites them.

18:22.039 --> 18:24.359
[ Chuckles ]
He was a bad dude.

18:24.400 --> 18:27.200
I don't think Andrew Thornton
was rebelling

18:27.240 --> 18:29.720
against his position in society.

18:29.759 --> 18:33.839
I think Andrew Thornton wanted
a different type of life.

18:33.880 --> 18:35.079
That's all it was.

18:35.119 --> 18:38.160
He saw himself
as being an adventurer,

18:38.200 --> 18:41.960
a person that literally
lived on the edge.

18:42.000 --> 18:45.519
Thornton helped create the myth
of Drew Thornton.

18:45.559 --> 18:49.599
He tried to build an image of
himself that was the superman.

18:49.640 --> 18:53.079
But it went beyond what he was
really capable of.

18:53.119 --> 18:56.079
Always a show-off,
Thornton liked to demonstrate

18:56.119 --> 18:57.680
his athletic arrest techniques

18:57.720 --> 19:00.240
to his buddies
in the police department.

19:00.279 --> 19:02.160
And so he tried
to jump over a car,

19:02.200 --> 19:04.839
and at the same time,
he was wearing a weapon.

19:04.880 --> 19:08.880
And the weapon went off,
and it ricocheted and shot him.

19:08.920 --> 19:11.759
[ Laughing ]

19:11.799 --> 19:13.680
♪

19:13.720 --> 19:16.759
It does no more than graze
his leg and his ego.

19:16.799 --> 19:19.440
But that doesn't stop him
from escalating his game

19:19.480 --> 19:23.079
from street dealing to flying
illegal drugs into Kentucky.

19:23.119 --> 19:27.240
♪

19:27.279 --> 19:29.519
I've been a pilot
for over 40 years,

19:29.559 --> 19:30.720
and then later I became

19:30.759 --> 19:33.119
an aviation writer
and photographer.

19:33.160 --> 19:35.079
♪

19:35.119 --> 19:37.440
I think one of the most
fascinating stories you'll find

19:37.480 --> 19:40.200
in drug smuggling
is the story of Drew Thornton.

19:40.240 --> 19:44.880
♪

19:44.920 --> 19:48.079
There's a personality type
who looks for a way

19:48.119 --> 19:51.039
to make life bigger.

19:51.079 --> 19:52.680
Sometime in the mid-'70s,

19:52.720 --> 19:56.920
Drew Thornton decided to move
beyond street level crime

19:56.960 --> 19:58.559
and become a smuggler.

19:58.599 --> 20:02.599
Drew was primarily bringing
really plane loads of marijuana

20:02.640 --> 20:05.400
into Kentucky for distribution
throughout the state.

20:05.440 --> 20:08.119
I mean, this was a big thing.

20:08.160 --> 20:10.799
They had devised a plan
that worked well.

20:10.839 --> 20:14.240
All they did was go get it,
transport it back,

20:14.279 --> 20:17.319
cut out the middle man.

20:17.359 --> 20:22.480
I would have never imagined
that this was happening.

20:22.519 --> 20:24.440
♪

20:24.480 --> 20:27.240
Through their contacts
in the Lexington drug scene,

20:27.279 --> 20:30.079
dirty cops Andrew Thornton
and Bill Canan

20:30.119 --> 20:32.920
establish a network
of out-of-state wholesalers

20:32.960 --> 20:37.319
who supply them
with larger quantities of pot.

20:37.359 --> 20:39.799
Thornton would be coming in
on the weekend,

20:39.839 --> 20:42.880
when a lot of recreational
flyers would be coming back in,

20:42.920 --> 20:45.839
so the radar scopes
would be full of airplanes.

20:45.880 --> 20:49.160
And you could easily
unload your luggage into a car,

20:49.200 --> 20:52.400
head up the highway,
and you're done.

20:52.440 --> 20:57.319
Drew Thornton flew in
many, many loads of marijuana.

20:57.359 --> 21:00.079
He was making
a substantial amount of money.

21:00.119 --> 21:04.720
♪

21:04.759 --> 21:09.880
As 1976 draws to a close, life
is good for the cocaine bear.

21:09.920 --> 21:12.960
But 200 miles away, things
are about to get complicated

21:13.000 --> 21:15.279
for our pair of dirty cops.

21:15.319 --> 21:21.880
♪

21:21.920 --> 21:24.680
In the late '70s, when
the narcotics squad in Lexington

21:24.720 --> 21:27.440
was cultivating people
who could become informants,

21:27.480 --> 21:30.559
one of those people
was Melanie Flynn.

21:30.599 --> 21:33.240
Melanie Flynn met Bill Canan,

21:33.279 --> 21:35.559
who was trying to use her
as an informant.

21:35.599 --> 21:38.079
She was furnishing him
with information

21:38.119 --> 21:40.079
about drug users and purchasers

21:40.119 --> 21:42.680
around the University
of Kentucky.

21:42.720 --> 21:43.759
Melanie by all accounts

21:43.799 --> 21:46.519
was just helping out
the local cops.

21:46.559 --> 21:48.920
She felt like this was
the right thing to do.

21:48.960 --> 21:52.480
Melanie doesn't know she
is working with crooked cops.

21:52.519 --> 21:54.160
But soon she begins to suspect

21:54.200 --> 21:56.480
that the drugs
circulating in Lexington

21:56.519 --> 22:00.039
are being supplied
by Drew Thornton and Bill Canan.

22:00.079 --> 22:01.839
And I think
they became concerned

22:01.880 --> 22:04.240
that she may be a threat
to their operations

22:04.279 --> 22:05.440
and would go to the authorities

22:05.480 --> 22:09.359
and cause them
some major problems.

22:09.400 --> 22:14.119
She leaves work one day
and is going home

22:14.160 --> 22:16.519
and is never seen again.

22:16.559 --> 22:23.400
♪

22:23.440 --> 22:25.400
Her car was later
found abandoned

22:25.440 --> 22:29.240
in an apartment complex
on the north side of Lexington.

22:29.279 --> 22:32.240
♪

22:32.279 --> 22:36.240
She was last seen
about two blocks away

22:36.279 --> 22:37.599
parked at an intersection,

22:37.640 --> 22:41.240
talking to two people
in a dark van.

22:41.279 --> 22:45.000
An investigation later
by Kentucky State Police,

22:45.039 --> 22:48.119
there was some belief that
maybe those two individuals

22:48.160 --> 22:50.880
had been Drew Thornton
and Bill Canan.

22:50.920 --> 22:54.880
♪

22:54.920 --> 22:56.559
When you go from drug smuggling

22:56.599 --> 22:58.839
and you escalate
to a crime of murder,

22:58.880 --> 23:01.880
that's really taken it
to a whole 'nother level.

23:01.920 --> 23:04.279
And that has not been proven yet

23:04.319 --> 23:07.640
of however Melanie Flynn
is still missing.

23:07.680 --> 23:14.480
♪

23:14.519 --> 23:21.200
♪

23:21.240 --> 23:23.400
After Melanie Flynn's
disappearance,

23:23.440 --> 23:24.720
a pocketbook
that she was carrying

23:24.759 --> 23:27.880
was found by a fisherman
in the Kentucky River.

23:27.920 --> 23:32.680
And in that were some
medications that were hers.

23:32.720 --> 23:36.319
Melanie Flynn is probably one
of the most tragic characters

23:36.359 --> 23:37.880
in all of this.

23:37.920 --> 23:40.799
To this day, we don't know
what really happened to her.

23:40.839 --> 23:46.000
And the rumor mill
was running very, very much.

23:46.039 --> 23:47.480
One rumor is that Drew Thornton

23:47.519 --> 23:50.880
is the subject of an internal
affairs investigation.

23:50.920 --> 23:52.559
He quits the police.

23:52.599 --> 23:55.640
Now he's free to move into
full-time smuggling...

23:55.680 --> 23:58.079
and the path is clearing
for his final flight

23:58.119 --> 24:00.519
over the woods of North Georgia.

24:06.319 --> 24:10.920
♪

24:10.960 --> 24:15.039
In the woods of North Georgia,
an innocent bear has no idea

24:15.079 --> 24:19.680
that there is a man 200 miles
away plotting something so huge

24:19.720 --> 24:23.680
that their worlds
will one day collide.

24:23.720 --> 24:28.920
I have heard many people say in
talking about Andrew Thornton,

24:28.960 --> 24:32.519
they would relate him
to the myth of Icarus

24:32.559 --> 24:34.759
flying too close to the sun.

24:34.799 --> 24:36.759
And that's exactly what he did.

24:36.799 --> 24:38.400
[ Chuckles ]

24:38.440 --> 24:42.440
♪

24:42.480 --> 24:46.680
By 1977, Drew Thornton
is no longer a cop

24:46.720 --> 24:49.519
and can now expand
his drug smuggling business

24:49.559 --> 24:52.880
with no one
looking over his shoulder.

24:52.920 --> 24:56.920
He thought of himself as
smarter than everybody else,

24:56.960 --> 24:58.200
had no fear.

24:58.240 --> 25:00.200
And he would push that envelope

25:00.240 --> 25:03.000
where many people
wouldn't do that.

25:03.039 --> 25:07.480
The only way for Thornton to
go big is to find new partners.

25:07.519 --> 25:10.279
He turns to an old friend
from Lexington,

25:10.319 --> 25:13.160
a man named Bradley Bryant.

25:13.200 --> 25:17.839
Bradley Bryant was a childhood
school friend of Drew Thornton.

25:17.880 --> 25:20.000
They went to the same
private school in Lexington,

25:20.039 --> 25:22.240
and they both went
to the military academy,

25:22.279 --> 25:24.480
so they had a long history.

25:24.519 --> 25:28.119
Bryant was even Thornton's
best man at his wedding.

25:28.160 --> 25:29.599
They were the salt of the earth.

25:29.640 --> 25:33.279
They were-- They were
the bastions of society.

25:33.319 --> 25:35.519
♪

25:35.559 --> 25:39.000
Bradley Bryant isn't just
an old buddy of Thornton's,

25:39.039 --> 25:40.960
he's a successful businessman

25:41.000 --> 25:44.279
with links to organized crime
all over the country.

25:44.319 --> 25:47.799
And he wants to be a player
in Sin City.

25:47.839 --> 25:53.799
♪

25:53.839 --> 25:57.240
Bradley Bryant
went to Las Vegas,

25:57.279 --> 26:02.799
and he met the Chagra brothers,
Lee and Jimmy Chagra.

26:02.839 --> 26:05.839
♪

26:05.880 --> 26:08.559
The Chagras were major,
major players

26:08.599 --> 26:11.200
in the drug business.

26:11.240 --> 26:16.599
They had connections with
South America, Mexico, Colombia.

26:16.640 --> 26:18.839
♪

26:18.880 --> 26:21.599
Jimmy and Lee Chagra
would allow Drew Thornton

26:21.640 --> 26:23.960
to import larger
amounts of marijuana.

26:24.000 --> 26:27.039
♪

26:27.079 --> 26:30.119
Andrew wasn't afraid to,
to go to South America

26:30.160 --> 26:31.799
and risk his life doing it.

26:31.839 --> 26:34.359
But I think that was part
of the attraction for him.

26:34.400 --> 26:39.640
♪

26:39.680 --> 26:42.200
If you're gonna bring in
tons of marijuana,

26:42.240 --> 26:45.720
you're gonna need an airplane
capable of hauling that.

26:45.759 --> 26:49.920
Drew Thornton was flying
a four-engine cargo aircraft,

26:49.960 --> 26:51.359
a World War II plane

26:51.400 --> 26:56.720
that was able to carry tons
of marijuana into Kentucky.

26:56.759 --> 26:59.519
Thornton's route takes him
from South America,

26:59.559 --> 27:04.240
up the coast of Florida,
and over North Georgia--

27:04.279 --> 27:06.960
the home territory
of the cocaine bear.

27:07.000 --> 27:08.599
[ Bear growls ]

27:08.640 --> 27:10.240
♪

27:10.279 --> 27:13.440
He was bringing in what's
estimated to be 10,000 pounds,

27:13.480 --> 27:17.599
five tons of marijuana.

27:17.640 --> 27:23.119
In today's money,
that's $5 million.

27:23.160 --> 27:24.640
These are Kentucky Blue Bloods

27:24.680 --> 27:27.200
that got together to go
into full-time smuggling

27:27.240 --> 27:29.000
and were pretty
successful at it.

27:29.039 --> 27:33.039
People don't understand
what a process it would be

27:33.079 --> 27:35.000
to fly into a foreign country,

27:35.039 --> 27:39.640
with a load of drugs coming back
to the United States of America.

27:39.680 --> 27:41.920
That takes a unique individual.

27:41.960 --> 27:45.640
They quickly ratcheted up
their business,

27:45.680 --> 27:48.200
becoming a major organization
in the southeast,

27:48.240 --> 27:50.079
maybe the biggest at that time.

27:50.119 --> 27:52.880
I mean, it was-- it-- it--

27:52.920 --> 27:54.759
it was unbelievable.

27:54.799 --> 27:59.680
♪

27:59.720 --> 28:02.960
Drew Thornton and Bradley
Bryant are raking in the cash

28:03.000 --> 28:06.880
on their way to the top of
the drug smuggling food chain.

28:06.920 --> 28:09.559
♪

28:09.599 --> 28:11.680
But they're so busy
living the high life,

28:11.720 --> 28:13.519
they ignore the warning signs

28:13.559 --> 28:16.359
that it's all about
to come crashing down.

28:16.400 --> 28:21.240
♪

28:21.279 --> 28:25.000
In 1978, Lee Chagra
was assassinated

28:25.039 --> 28:27.200
in his office.

28:27.240 --> 28:30.319
The suspicion was obviously
that it was a retaliation

28:30.359 --> 28:33.319
for some crime
that had gone bad.

28:33.359 --> 28:34.680
Lee Chagra's death brings

28:34.720 --> 28:37.680
unwanted police attention
for Thornton.

28:37.720 --> 28:42.519
Within months, Jimmy Chagra is
arrested for drug trafficking.

28:42.559 --> 28:45.000
And this sets in motion
a bizarre series of events

28:45.039 --> 28:49.200
that will send Thornton's life
into free-fall.

28:49.240 --> 28:53.519
Jimmy Chagra was to go on trial
for his criminal activities.

28:53.559 --> 28:56.400
That trial that would be under
the, uh, supervision

28:56.440 --> 28:59.039
of Judge John Wood.

28:59.079 --> 29:00.799
Was often known as Maximum John

29:00.839 --> 29:03.400
for the sentences
he would hand out.

29:03.440 --> 29:06.400
The day before the trial
was scheduled to start,

29:06.440 --> 29:09.799
Judge Wood was assassinated
in his driveway.

29:09.839 --> 29:13.240
♪

29:13.279 --> 29:16.000
Judge John Wood was fatally
wounded by a single gunshot

29:16.039 --> 29:18.000
as he was getting in his car
this morning.

29:18.039 --> 29:19.920
Emergency attendants
worked on the judge

29:19.960 --> 29:21.799
but could not revive him.

29:21.839 --> 29:27.359
♪

29:27.400 --> 29:30.519
John Wood was assassinated
by a hit man

29:30.559 --> 29:33.839
hired by Jimmy Chagra.

29:33.880 --> 29:36.240
It's hard to imagine
what Thornton's associate

29:36.279 --> 29:40.000
was thinking
when he ordered the hit.

29:40.039 --> 29:43.240
It didn't make a lot of sense
in many, many ways.

29:43.279 --> 29:46.559
It just simply wasn't done.

29:46.599 --> 29:50.519
People just didn't
do things like that.

29:50.559 --> 29:54.319
Perhaps it was scare tactics,
but it didn't work.

29:54.359 --> 29:57.680
Jimmy Chagra went down
for 30 years.

29:57.720 --> 30:02.200
But that's not the strangest
twist in this assassination.

30:02.240 --> 30:07.960
Chagra had hired a gentleman
named Charles Harrelson.

30:08.000 --> 30:10.759
If the name Charles Harrelson
is familiar,

30:10.799 --> 30:14.359
it's because the hit man
has a Hollywood connection.

30:14.400 --> 30:19.279
He's the father of actor
Woody Harrelson.

30:19.319 --> 30:23.000
♪

30:23.039 --> 30:25.640
The Wood killing
was international news.

30:25.680 --> 30:27.359
Everybody in law enforcement
in the United States

30:27.400 --> 30:28.680
knew about it.

30:28.720 --> 30:30.640
That was a line
that had not been crossed.

30:30.680 --> 30:33.559
A lot of attention was on
anything that happened to do

30:33.599 --> 30:37.039
with the Chagra Brothers,
including Drew Thornton.

30:37.079 --> 30:41.079
Suddenly Drew Thornton of
little-old Lexington, Kentucky,

30:41.119 --> 30:43.519
is on the radar of the FBI.

30:43.559 --> 30:45.960
There's nowhere left to hide.

30:53.400 --> 30:58.160
♪

30:58.200 --> 31:02.519
The cocaine bear was the second
case that was worked in Georgia

31:02.559 --> 31:06.839
where an animal had come
to its demise from cocaine.

31:10.039 --> 31:13.200
In September of 1982,
the sheriff's office had called

31:13.240 --> 31:18.039
and said a farmer had found
a blue canister cylinder

31:18.079 --> 31:21.519
in his pasture with his cows.

31:21.559 --> 31:24.880
And his cows had gotten
into the cylinder.

31:24.920 --> 31:25.920
[ Cow moos ]

31:25.960 --> 31:27.880
And I said are you crazy?

31:27.920 --> 31:31.279
The cows had white powder
all over their noses.

31:31.319 --> 31:35.039
♪

31:35.079 --> 31:37.880
There's something going on here.

31:37.920 --> 31:41.279
But where did the cows
get their cocaine?

31:41.319 --> 31:43.079
[ Cow grunts ]

31:46.359 --> 31:50.599
Could it be the same supplier
to our legendary bear?

31:52.039 --> 31:56.759
♪

31:56.799 --> 32:01.519
But back in 1980, Drew Thornton
isn't a cocaine smuggler.

32:03.240 --> 32:07.279
He's running marijuana

32:07.319 --> 32:09.319
and lots of it.

32:09.359 --> 32:12.480
♪

32:12.519 --> 32:14.559
After the murder
of a federal judge,

32:14.599 --> 32:18.839
Thornton becomes a person
of interest for the FBI.

32:18.880 --> 32:20.680
♪

32:20.720 --> 32:23.480
We got notified immediately
from FBI headquarters

32:23.519 --> 32:25.079
that a federal judge
had been murdered,

32:25.119 --> 32:29.279
and there might be a person
in Lexington involved in that.

32:29.319 --> 32:31.799
The FBI has the killer

32:31.839 --> 32:34.960
and the man who ordered the hit.

32:35.000 --> 32:38.920
Now they are shaking down
all of his criminal contacts.

32:40.200 --> 32:42.799
But despite the heat,

32:42.839 --> 32:45.039
Thornton and his old buddy
Bradley Bryant

32:45.079 --> 32:47.000
are still smuggling.

32:47.039 --> 32:50.400
Thornton was living
a very, very good life,

32:50.440 --> 32:53.880
and Bryant was after the money.

32:53.920 --> 32:55.480
So they gambled.

32:55.519 --> 32:58.519
And that's an old Kentucky vice,
of course.

32:58.559 --> 33:02.799
They gambled, and they lost,
and they lost big time.

33:02.839 --> 33:10.319
♪

33:10.359 --> 33:15.279
In 1981 at a hotel
at the Philadelphia airport,

33:15.319 --> 33:18.559
Bradley Bryant's luck ran out.

33:18.599 --> 33:21.880
He was arrested
with a huge supply

33:21.920 --> 33:25.960
of automatic weapons,
night vision goggles,

33:26.000 --> 33:27.920
and sophisticated
communication gear,

33:27.960 --> 33:30.000
something that one
federal agent told me

33:30.039 --> 33:33.920
looked a lot like
a complicated assassination kit.

33:33.960 --> 33:36.759
Another weapons stash
is discovered by the feds

33:36.799 --> 33:39.880
in a Lexington warehouse
owned by Bryant.

33:39.920 --> 33:46.880
♪

33:46.920 --> 33:51.880
He's sentenced
to 15 years in jail,

33:51.920 --> 33:55.680
and there's bad news for
the drug operation's star pilot.

33:56.960 --> 33:59.759
Hidden among the weapons
is a notebook.

33:59.799 --> 34:02.920
Written inside
is the name Andrew Thornton,

34:02.960 --> 34:07.319
along with code words for
marijuana smuggling missions.

34:07.359 --> 34:08.760
Thornton became fearful

34:08.800 --> 34:12.880
for the attention that was gonna
come to bear on him.

34:12.920 --> 34:15.039
He immediately
dropped outta sight.

34:15.079 --> 34:17.679
♪

34:17.719 --> 34:20.079
It turned out
that he was on the run,

34:20.119 --> 34:23.840
and he was still up to his old
tricks, flying his airplane.

34:23.880 --> 34:28.159
♪

34:28.199 --> 34:33.440
For months, Thornton flies
from airport to airport,

34:33.480 --> 34:36.880
staying under the radar
and avoiding capture.

34:38.400 --> 34:40.480
Thornton liked
the idea of risk.

34:40.519 --> 34:45.679
He loved excitement,
he loved adventure.

34:45.719 --> 34:49.440
He would have
enjoyed that immensely.

34:49.480 --> 34:56.079
♪

34:56.119 --> 34:58.000
He landed at an airport
in North Carolina,

34:58.039 --> 35:00.920
and customs officials were
intercepting his communication

35:00.960 --> 35:02.400
and tracking his flights.

35:02.440 --> 35:05.719
[ Indistinct radio chatter ]

35:05.760 --> 35:07.480
And that's where they got him.

35:07.519 --> 35:14.480
♪

35:14.519 --> 35:16.840
But he wasn't caught with drugs.

35:16.880 --> 35:18.679
♪

35:18.719 --> 35:22.199
Thornton's plane
is completely clean.

35:22.239 --> 35:24.079
Someone could have
tipped him off...

35:24.119 --> 35:27.880
or he just got lucky.

35:27.920 --> 35:34.199
Thornton was a very, very, very
lucky man in many, many ways.

35:34.239 --> 35:36.119
The evidence against him
is thin.

35:36.159 --> 35:38.840
Thornton was under suspicion
for drug trafficking.

35:38.880 --> 35:41.440
He was indicted for
a conspiracy involving drugs,

35:41.480 --> 35:45.639
pleaded no contest to a single
count of marijuana smuggling.

35:45.679 --> 35:50.079
Thornton gets off easy
and only serves five months.

35:50.119 --> 35:53.639
♪

35:53.679 --> 35:55.480
With all his friends in prison,

35:55.519 --> 35:58.639
Thornton's marijuana empire
has collapsed.

35:58.679 --> 36:01.920
But he's not ready
to give up just yet.

36:01.960 --> 36:04.039
♪

36:04.079 --> 36:06.360
That's when Drew Thornton
became the lone wolf.

36:06.400 --> 36:08.599
He used what connections he had

36:08.639 --> 36:12.119
to start bringing in cocaine...

36:12.159 --> 36:14.079
[ Bear growls ]

36:14.119 --> 36:16.599
...which changed everything.

36:16.639 --> 36:18.800
[ Indistinct conversations ]

36:18.840 --> 36:21.239
♪

36:21.280 --> 36:23.960
In the '70s, there was
a huge appetite for marijuana

36:24.000 --> 36:26.039
in the United States,

36:26.079 --> 36:30.760
but then in the '80s,
the appetite shifted to cocaine.

36:30.800 --> 36:31.960
It became the drug of choice.

36:32.000 --> 36:33.800
A lot of celebrities
were using it,

36:33.840 --> 36:38.079
and it was attractive
for the smugglers.

36:38.119 --> 36:40.599
I joined DEA in 1983,

36:40.639 --> 36:45.599
I was assigned to working
drug cases throughout Kentucky

36:45.639 --> 36:48.920
that took me to South America.

36:48.960 --> 36:54.480
Once I joined DEA, I learned
a lot about Andrew Thornton.

36:54.519 --> 36:57.280
Andrew went from flying
tons of marijuana

36:57.320 --> 36:59.920
to flying kilos of cocaine,

36:59.960 --> 37:01.920
because it took
a much smaller airplane,

37:01.960 --> 37:05.280
which was less noticeable
by law enforcement.

37:05.320 --> 37:08.519
You could make 10 times the
amount of money easily on a run

37:08.559 --> 37:10.280
that you would with marijuana.

37:10.320 --> 37:13.880
And a pilot like Drew Thornton
could do everything on his own.

37:13.920 --> 37:18.079
♪

37:18.119 --> 37:23.159
By 1983, Thornton's using
his connections in Colombia

37:23.199 --> 37:26.559
to smuggle cocaine into America.

37:26.599 --> 37:29.480
I knew that he was
a major drug smuggler.

37:29.519 --> 37:31.760
And several agencies
were working

37:31.800 --> 37:35.280
to build a case
against Andrew Thornton.

37:35.320 --> 37:39.039
He's now set for the flight
that will make him infamous

37:39.079 --> 37:43.519
and forever connected
to the fate of the cocaine bear.

37:49.559 --> 37:53.800
♪

37:53.840 --> 37:58.519
It's 1985, and Andrew Thornton
is back in the big time,

37:58.559 --> 38:01.880
smuggling cocaine into Kentucky.

38:01.920 --> 38:04.440
But in the legend
of the cocaine bear,

38:04.480 --> 38:06.800
his fate is sealed,

38:06.840 --> 38:09.280
and his end is fast approaching.

38:09.320 --> 38:16.599
♪

38:16.639 --> 38:21.039
On the night of September
the 10th, 1985,

38:21.079 --> 38:25.199
he flew a load of cocaine into
the United States from Colombia.

38:25.239 --> 38:27.440
♪

38:27.480 --> 38:32.440
His goal was to move cocaine
into the Lexington area,

38:32.480 --> 38:34.880
with an intermediate
stop in Georgia

38:34.920 --> 38:37.119
where he had
some co-conspirators

38:37.159 --> 38:39.239
waiting to offload
the airplane.

38:39.280 --> 38:40.920
You just don't get in a plane
and fly to Colombia

38:40.960 --> 38:43.039
and pick up a load
of cocaine and come back.

38:43.079 --> 38:46.840
This would have taken
some serious prior planning.

38:46.880 --> 38:48.679
♪

38:48.719 --> 38:51.280
Thornton's journey
started as planned.

38:51.320 --> 38:53.679
He passed Cuba and navigated
the coast of Florida

38:53.719 --> 38:56.559
without incident.

38:56.599 --> 38:59.480
But what happened next?

38:59.519 --> 39:03.119
There are certain facts upon
which most investigators agree.

39:03.159 --> 39:06.719
♪

39:06.760 --> 39:10.320
Thornton did not make
his landing in Georgia.

39:10.360 --> 39:13.039
Was flying over
the National Forest in Georgia

39:13.079 --> 39:16.440
and started throwing out
cocaine into the forest.

39:16.480 --> 39:18.960
♪

39:19.000 --> 39:22.320
Probably worth
hundreds of millions.

39:22.360 --> 39:25.599
He attached the duffel bags
to parachutes,

39:25.639 --> 39:27.239
pushed them out of the airplane,

39:27.280 --> 39:31.360
and then he had about 75 pounds
of cocaine strapped to his body.

39:31.400 --> 39:33.280
♪

39:33.320 --> 39:35.920
And then with the remaining
cocaine strapped to him,

39:35.960 --> 39:38.440
he put the airplane on autopilot

39:38.480 --> 39:42.199
somewhere near the Knoxville
downtown airport, jumped...

39:45.400 --> 39:50.159
And then something happened
that he didn't expect to happen.

39:50.199 --> 39:51.880
[ Thud ]

39:58.960 --> 40:02.679
How did Andrew Thornton
parachute to his death?

40:05.840 --> 40:08.039
People do have a number
of different theories

40:08.079 --> 40:10.559
to how this happened,
why it went bad.

40:10.599 --> 40:14.239
♪

40:14.280 --> 40:15.559
The most common story I heard

40:15.599 --> 40:18.239
was that the main chute
did not fully open

40:18.280 --> 40:20.639
for unknown reasons.

40:20.679 --> 40:24.480
The reserve chute
also did not fully inflate.

40:24.519 --> 40:28.000
♪

40:28.039 --> 40:30.760
People noted at the time
that there was an obvious cut

40:30.800 --> 40:34.119
or bruise on his head,
and so perhaps he hit his head

40:34.159 --> 40:37.320
going out the door
of the airplane.

40:37.360 --> 40:38.679
He was unconscious,

40:38.719 --> 40:41.760
didn't have an opportunity
to pull his chute.

40:41.800 --> 40:43.760
It also may have had
something to do with

40:43.800 --> 40:46.400
Thornton carrying
all that cocaine on him.

40:46.440 --> 40:49.519
♪

40:49.559 --> 40:54.599
From the injuries to his face,
the medical examiner believed

40:54.639 --> 40:57.800
that load of cocaine
had swung back around

40:57.840 --> 41:00.039
and caught him in the face
and either knocked him out

41:00.079 --> 41:02.719
or addled him
to where he was confused.

41:02.760 --> 41:05.800
You know, so, it would be
a pretty good lick.

41:08.880 --> 41:13.039
But what compelled Thornton
to jump out of the plane?

41:13.079 --> 41:15.239
The word on the street was
he felt like

41:15.280 --> 41:18.440
he was being surveilled
by customs or DEA.

41:18.480 --> 41:20.480
[ Indistinct radio chatter ]

41:20.519 --> 41:23.440
Somewhere along the way,
he became paranoid

41:23.480 --> 41:27.199
that he were being followed
or being tracked by a DEA plane

41:27.239 --> 41:29.599
or Coast Guard or customs.

41:29.639 --> 41:31.840
A lot of people think
he probably jumped out

41:31.880 --> 41:35.440
of the airplane
because of his paranoia.

41:35.480 --> 41:38.039
♪

41:38.079 --> 41:41.480
But we checked, and they did not
have any aircraft

41:41.519 --> 41:44.119
following him
into the United States.

41:47.880 --> 41:52.440
If law enforcement wasn't
on his tail, why jump at all?

41:52.480 --> 41:55.840
♪

41:55.880 --> 41:59.639
I think this was his plan
all along.

41:59.679 --> 42:01.519
One of the stories
that was circulating

42:01.559 --> 42:05.440
was that he actually was ripping
off the Colombian suppliers

42:05.480 --> 42:07.960
by intentionally
crashing the airplane,

42:08.000 --> 42:10.280
claiming the cocaine
was destroyed in the crash,

42:10.320 --> 42:12.199
but keeping it for himself.

42:12.239 --> 42:14.840
Why would he have all those
parachutes in the airplane

42:14.880 --> 42:17.000
tied to duffel bags
full of cocaine

42:17.039 --> 42:20.239
if that wasn't
the plan originally?

42:20.280 --> 42:21.760
No, I don't think so.

42:21.800 --> 42:26.039
He was way too smart to steal
from the Medellin Cartel.

42:26.079 --> 42:27.639
They knew who he was.

42:27.679 --> 42:31.440
He-- He would have not lasted
very long at all

42:31.480 --> 42:34.440
if he had stolen from them.

42:34.480 --> 42:39.519
Whether Thornton was scamming
the cartels or just paranoid,

42:39.559 --> 42:41.239
there's one even more
shocking theory

42:41.280 --> 42:44.239
about what happened that night.

42:44.280 --> 42:45.440
One of the theories is that

42:45.480 --> 42:48.119
there was a second person
on the airplane.

42:48.159 --> 42:55.039
♪

42:55.079 --> 42:58.199
We initially thought that
other people were involved,

42:58.239 --> 43:01.159
but we didn't have any proof.

43:01.199 --> 43:04.880
This is the downtown
Knoxville Island Home airport.

43:04.920 --> 43:08.920
Where Mr. Thornton parachuted
into the residential area

43:08.960 --> 43:12.239
is about 250 yards
as the crow flies

43:12.280 --> 43:15.000
above us on the hill.

43:15.039 --> 43:18.239
About two or three months
after Thornton was found,

43:18.280 --> 43:24.079
another parachute was found
on the far end of the runway.

43:24.119 --> 43:26.639
We theorized
that Andrew Thornton

43:26.679 --> 43:30.239
let the other individual
in the plane jump.

43:30.280 --> 43:33.039
And then Thornton put
the plane on autopilot.

43:33.079 --> 43:35.760
He would jump out of the plane
and let it go across

43:35.800 --> 43:39.679
the mountains
in North Carolina and crash.

43:39.719 --> 43:41.639
If there was one other person
on the plane,

43:41.679 --> 43:44.519
it would've to be someone
that Drew Thornton trusted.

43:44.559 --> 43:45.880
And I don't know
of anybody back then

43:45.920 --> 43:48.360
that he trusted
more than Bill Canan.

43:48.400 --> 43:50.199
♪

43:50.239 --> 43:53.119
Canan's his very close friend
who worked alongside him

43:53.159 --> 43:55.719
at the Lexington
Police Department.

43:55.760 --> 43:58.639
Was Thornton's old partner,
corrupt cop Bill Canan,

43:58.679 --> 44:00.760
with him at the very end?

44:00.800 --> 44:03.239
Canan was
the most likely suspect

44:03.280 --> 44:07.199
until someone else came forward,
uh, also named Bill

44:07.239 --> 44:10.079
who, uh, professed
that he was on the plane.

44:10.119 --> 44:13.280
♪

44:13.320 --> 44:17.239
In 1990, a man named Bill
Leonard told an amazing story

44:17.280 --> 44:20.320
to a journalist at
the Knoxville News Sentinel.

44:20.360 --> 44:23.000
♪

44:23.039 --> 44:27.320
Thornton had talked Bill
Leonard into travelling with him

44:27.360 --> 44:29.519
to help provide
security for him.

44:29.559 --> 44:32.599
But apparently Leonard thought
that was gonna be in Florida

44:32.639 --> 44:35.039
or The Bahamas,
but Thornton kept flying,

44:35.079 --> 44:38.880
and they ended up in Colombia,
surprising Bill Leonard.

44:38.920 --> 44:42.159
♪

44:42.199 --> 44:44.920
You have to ask yourself
how plausible that is.

44:44.960 --> 44:48.599
But, you know, the Bill Leonard
that I knew was a stand-up guy,

44:48.639 --> 44:51.840
and you could believe him.

44:51.880 --> 44:54.199
Leonard has never been
charged with a crime.

44:54.239 --> 44:56.599
And I spoke to former detectives
from Lexington

44:56.639 --> 44:58.440
who believe his story.

44:58.480 --> 45:01.800
They're convinced that he was
an unwitting accomplice

45:01.840 --> 45:05.159
in that smuggling run.

45:05.199 --> 45:07.039
I don't know how you account
for the fact

45:07.079 --> 45:09.920
that someone as experienced
as Drew Thornton

45:09.960 --> 45:12.639
as a paratrooper
did not survive that night

45:12.679 --> 45:16.280
and the totally inexperienced
Bill Leonard did.

45:16.320 --> 45:19.800
Pure luck? Perhaps.

45:19.840 --> 45:21.760
I've asked a number
of the investigators

45:21.800 --> 45:23.119
from the federal aviation

45:23.159 --> 45:25.840
to the FBI to the state police
in Tennessee.

45:25.880 --> 45:27.840
Nobody has any answer.

45:27.880 --> 45:29.400
♪

45:29.440 --> 45:31.760
Much of what happened
in the skies over Knoxville

45:31.800 --> 45:35.039
remains a mystery.

45:35.079 --> 45:38.760
Can more answers
be found in North Georgia?

45:38.800 --> 45:41.880
And what really happened
to the cocaine bear?

45:49.760 --> 45:52.119
♪

45:52.159 --> 45:55.880
On Andrew Thornton's
final flight in 1985,

45:55.920 --> 45:58.639
he drops several duffel bags
full of cocaine

45:58.679 --> 46:02.119
over the Southern United States.

46:02.159 --> 46:03.519
There was a map

46:03.559 --> 46:05.920
that showed where the cocaine
was found along the way.

46:05.960 --> 46:09.840
And you could just about
track his line of flight

46:09.880 --> 46:12.280
where the packages
were thrown out.

46:12.320 --> 46:18.679
♪

46:18.719 --> 46:21.719
One lands in the woods that are
the home of the cocaine bear.

46:21.760 --> 46:23.119
[ Bear growls ]

46:23.159 --> 46:25.679
One of the DEA agents
called back and said,

46:25.719 --> 46:27.719
"You know that a bear

46:27.760 --> 46:29.960
got into that cocaine down there
in the woods."

46:30.000 --> 46:32.199
And I was like, "Oh, come on."

46:32.239 --> 46:35.360
And at first I thought that,
you know, that was, they were,

46:35.400 --> 46:37.719
they were kind of gigging me
a little bit,

46:37.760 --> 46:39.960
but actually, it did happen.

46:40.000 --> 46:45.000
♪

46:45.039 --> 46:47.920
When Fran Wiley's officers
get to the scene,

46:47.960 --> 46:51.800
there is no cocaine left.

46:51.840 --> 46:54.920
She has her own theory
about what happened to it.

46:54.960 --> 46:58.840
There was no cocaine
in the duffel bag at the scene.

46:58.880 --> 47:01.679
So where did the cocaine go?

47:01.719 --> 47:02.960
Well, the bear ate it.

47:03.000 --> 47:05.760
Well, no,
the bear didn't ate it.

47:05.800 --> 47:07.719
The bad guys got it.

47:07.760 --> 47:10.800
♪

47:10.840 --> 47:14.159
The bear would've never
been able to consume

47:14.199 --> 47:16.239
75 pounds of cocaine.

47:16.280 --> 47:19.800
The pathologist told me
that it had consumed

47:19.840 --> 47:22.840
about 3 grams of cocaine

47:22.880 --> 47:26.920
that was 95% pure.

47:26.960 --> 47:29.920
It would probably
would have been dead

47:29.960 --> 47:32.639
within the first or second bite.

47:32.679 --> 47:35.519
♪

47:35.559 --> 47:41.400
My theory is that Mr. Thornton
had a predestined location

47:41.440 --> 47:46.719
for his ground crew
to pick up the cocaine.

47:46.760 --> 47:49.840
And I think that they did.

47:49.880 --> 47:52.679
They probably saw the bear
had got into it.

47:52.719 --> 47:56.119
♪

47:56.159 --> 47:59.039
And they picked up
the remaining and left.

48:04.119 --> 48:12.880
♪

48:12.920 --> 48:17.239
I've heard many variations
of this story

48:17.280 --> 48:19.639
about the bear

48:19.679 --> 48:23.280
in Lexington, Kentucky,
that is on display.

48:23.320 --> 48:25.280
♪

48:25.320 --> 48:29.239
They are portraying it
to be Pablo EskoBear.

48:29.280 --> 48:35.360
♪

48:35.400 --> 48:37.840
But that is not my bear.

48:37.880 --> 48:39.480
There's no way.

48:39.519 --> 48:41.360
♪

48:41.400 --> 48:46.119
The bear was in no condition
to be taxidermied.

48:46.159 --> 48:48.840
I think the purveyors
of the display,

48:48.880 --> 48:50.360
if you press them,
they would tell you

48:50.400 --> 48:52.800
that it's not the same bear.

48:52.840 --> 48:54.880
It's symbolic.

48:54.920 --> 48:57.719
So, what do the mall's
owners say?

48:57.760 --> 49:00.159
They claim that
their "taxidermy bear

49:00.199 --> 49:03.840
is 100% Cocaine Bear,"

49:03.880 --> 49:06.159
and that "if disbelief
is your choice,

49:06.199 --> 49:09.519
then we created
the most fantastic story ever."

49:09.559 --> 49:15.760
♪

49:15.800 --> 49:18.000
The whereabouts of
the real cocaine bear

49:18.039 --> 49:22.920
is as mysterious
as so much of this legend.

49:22.960 --> 49:26.239
The story begins with reports
of a dead parachutist

49:26.280 --> 49:28.719
found wearing Gucci loafers,

49:28.760 --> 49:31.760
and even that may be a myth.

49:31.800 --> 49:33.159
There were incorrect accounts

49:33.199 --> 49:37.679
as to what exactly
he was wearing on his feet.

49:37.719 --> 49:41.039
There was one indication
that he had Gucci loafers.

49:41.079 --> 49:44.239
In reality, Thornton's
shoes were described

49:44.280 --> 49:48.360
as the "Gucci loafers"
of the parachuting world.

49:48.400 --> 49:54.079
He had some very expensive
jumping shoes on.

49:54.119 --> 49:58.119
When I was told about them,
they were equated to Gucci.

49:58.159 --> 49:59.880
That's how they tried
to correlate it to me

49:59.920 --> 50:02.199
was this would be like Gucci.

50:02.239 --> 50:06.320
♪

50:06.360 --> 50:09.599
I don't think we'll ever know
what really happened.

50:09.639 --> 50:12.599
I think we have
gotten pretty close

50:12.639 --> 50:13.960
with the bits and pieces

50:14.000 --> 50:15.719
and the puzzles
that we've put together.

50:15.760 --> 50:17.800
With the individuals
that are still alive

50:17.840 --> 50:20.800
and the agencies that did
the legwork that they did,

50:20.840 --> 50:24.480
I think we got as close
to knowing what happened

50:24.519 --> 50:27.760
as we ever will.

50:27.800 --> 50:30.719
A curtain was drawn
over the conspiracy,

50:30.760 --> 50:34.480
the drugs, the murders.

50:34.519 --> 50:37.920
If I had to go to my grave
with that on my conscience,

50:37.960 --> 50:40.199
I would not want
to stand very tall

50:40.239 --> 50:43.159
on the day of judgment
is all I can say.

50:43.199 --> 50:45.320
♪

50:45.360 --> 50:49.559
Bradley Bryant served his time
and then dropped out of sight.

50:49.599 --> 50:54.840
Bill Canan was jailed in 1994
for federal drug charges.

50:54.880 --> 50:57.360
He passed away in 2020.

50:57.400 --> 51:02.960
♪

51:03.000 --> 51:06.519
And as for Drew Thornton,
his myth lives on,

51:06.559 --> 51:10.599
alongside that
of the cocaine bear.

51:10.639 --> 51:12.239
He was a bad guy.

51:12.280 --> 51:16.079
These guys
did this stuff for fun,

51:16.119 --> 51:19.840
and, and that's kind of scary.

51:19.880 --> 51:23.119
Thinking about Andrew Thornton
and the cocaine bear,

51:23.159 --> 51:27.360
would've Thornton liked to have
been associated with that?

51:27.400 --> 51:28.840
I think he would've thought

51:28.880 --> 51:30.880
the bear was getting
more attention than he did,

51:30.920 --> 51:33.400
and I don't think he would've
liked that whatsoever.

51:33.440 --> 51:36.440
But he probably would've been
amused by it.

51:36.480 --> 51:42.119
♪
